    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>2 Microsofts: The Right Thing?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kevin O'Driscoll letter say obvious solution to dissolving Microsoft's dominance of software market would be for government to mandate entry of Windows operating system into public domain (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''U.S. and 17 States Ask Judge to Cut Microsoft in 2 Parts; Serious Curbs Also Sought'' (front page, April 29): The obvious solution to dissolving Microsoft's dominance of the software market would be for the government to mandate entry of the Windows operating system code into the public domain, where it truly belongs. Microsoft has profited immensely and for an extended period of time from this product and its market dominance.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''U.S. and 17 States Ask Judge to Cut Microsoft in 2 Parts; Serious Curbs Also Sought'' (front page, April 29): The obvious solution to dissolving Microsoft's dominance of the software market would be for the government to mandate entry of the Windows operating system code into the public domain, where it truly belongs. Microsoft has profited immensely and for an extended period of time from this product and its market dominance.</p>
        <p>Microsoft should be compelled to allow fair competition by allowing any and all comers to use its nearly ubiquitous Windows platform.</p>
        <p>KEVIN O'DRISCOLL  New York, April 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
